metadata.title: Millions of Americans Fear Eviction as Moratorium Expires
metadata.description: Estimated number of U.S. adults in rental housing behind on rent and their perceived eviction risk (as of July 2021)
metadata.main_insight: As of July 2021, 7.43 million US adults were behind on rent, and a significant number of them (3.65m) believed they were somewhat or very likely to be evicted in the next two months.
